<title>USA: Cell Robotics gets FDA OK for erbium laser.</title>
<headline>Cell Robotics gets FDA OK for erbium laser.</headline>
<dateline>ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. 1997-07-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Cell Robotics International Inc said Wednesday it received clearance from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration to market its erbium laser for dermatology and other applications.</p>
<p>The company said the laser is approved for joint arthroscopy, vaporizing and coagulation of soft tissue and general procedures for cutting, including hair removal and cosmetic surgery.</p>
<p>The laser, which should be available for delivery in the fall, is lightweight and affordable, Cell Robotics said.</p>
